\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Memory Allocation Strategy\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 To prevent memory pressure and swapping, the system should follow a sequential loading protocol.\
The approximate memory footprint ($M$) can be calculated as:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 $$M_\{total\} \\approx (P_\{LLM\} \\times B_\{LLM\}) + (P_\{Diff\} \\times B_\{Diff\}) + M_\{OS\}$$\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Where $P$ is the parameter count and $B$ is the bits-per-weight. For this 24GB build, we target a combined footprint of 
\f1\b ~16\'9618GB
\f0\b0  to leave headroom for the macOS window server and thermal management.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
